tm_term%3D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupdated%20regulatory%20text%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20proposal%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-long-will-take-cancel-student-debt-higher-education-act-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancel%20student%20debt%20using%20the%20Higher%20Education%20Act%20of%201965%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20struck%20down%20Biden's%20first%20attempt%20at%20broad%20debt%20relief%20at%20the%20end%20of%20June%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20immediately%20started%20its%20second%20attempt%20at%20relief%20using%20the%20HEA%20%E2%80%94%20a%20law%20that%20requires%20a%20series%20of%20negotiation%20sessions%20with%20stakeholders%20to%20help%20craft%20the%20final%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20has%20so%20far%20held%20two%20negotiation%20sessions%20in%20October%20and%20November%2C%20and%20the%20final%20two-day%20session%20will%20occur%20on%20December%2011%20and%2012.%20During%20those%20days%2C%20negotiators%20will%20discuss%20the%20department's%20proposed%20plan%20for%20relief.%20The%20latest%20iteration%20of%20the%20text%20plans%20to%20prioritize%20these%20five%20groups%20of%20borrowers%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EBorrowers%20on%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%20who%20have%20balances%20that%20are%20greater%20than%20what%20they%20originally%20owed.%20The%20department%20proposes%20waiving%20up%20to%20%2420%2C000%20of%20that%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20borrowers%20who%20have%20balances%20greater%20than%20what%20they%20owed%20upon%20entering%20repayment.%20The%20department%20proposes%20waiving%20up%20to%20%2410%2C000%20for%20those%20borrowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EBorrowers%20whose%20loans%20entered%20repayment%20decades%20ago.%20The%20department%20proposes%20one-time%20relief%2020%20years%20after%20entering%20repayment%20for%20borrowers%20with%20undergraduate%20loans.%20All%20other%20borrowers%20who%20have%20been%20in%20repayment%20for%2025%20years%20would%20also%20be%20eligible%20for%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EBorrowers%20who%20are%20eligible%20for%20relief%20under%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%20or%20targeted%20programs%20like%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%2C%20but%20haven't%20applied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EBorrowers%20who%20attended%20schools%20that%20left%20them%20with%20unaffordable%20debt%20compared%20to%20post-grad%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStudent%20loans%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20bridge%20to%20a%20better%20life%2C%20not%20a%20life%20sentence%20of%20endless%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20Education%20Secretary%20Miguel%20Cardona%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThis%20rulemaking%20process%20is%20about%20standing%20up%20for%20borrowers%20who've%20been%20failed%20by%20the%20country's%20broken%20student%20loan%20system%20and%20creating%20new%20regulations%20that%20will%20reduce%20the%20burden%20of%20student%20debt%20in%20this%20country.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20updated%20text%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loans-debt-forgiveness-who-qualifies-borrowers-relief-education-department-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslightly%20differs%20from%20the%20department's%20proposals%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20November%20negotiation%20session%20in%20that%20it%20does%20not%20define%20certain%20hardships%20that%20would%20qualify%20borrowers%20for%20relief.%20During%20the%20November%20session%2C%20the%20negotiators%20spent%20time%20providing%20definitions%20of%20hardship%20qualifications%2C%20but%20the%20department%20said%20in%20its%20press%20release%20that%20the%20current%20text%20will%20not%20include%20that%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Department%20will%20consider%20ways%20to%20pursue%20relief%20for%20this%20category%20of%20borrowers%20and%20has%20dedicated%20time%20to%20address%20this%20issue%20during%20the%20December%20session%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20press%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20December%20session%2C%20the%20negotiating%20committee%20will%20determine%20if%20it%20reached%20consensus%20on%20each%20individual%20idea%20the%20department%20proposed.%20Following%20consensus%2C%20the%20department%20will%20start%20working%20on%20its%20draft%20rules%20before%20publishing%20it%20for%20public%20comment%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20plan%20for%20relief%20is%20more%20narrow%20than%20Biden's%20first%20attempt%2C%20many%20borrowers%20experiencing%20different%20forms%20of%20hardship%20hope%20they'll%20qualify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20wife's%20car%2C%20plus%20food%2C%20plus%20utilities%2C%20plus%20the%20mortgage%2C%20plus%20the%20car%20payment%2C%26quot%3B%20one%2063-year-old%20borrower%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaying-off-student-loans-medical-bills-debt-cancellation-biden-relief-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20too%20many%20payments%20and%20if%20I%20don't%20qualify%20for%20hardship%2C%20I%20just%20don't%20know%20what%20I'm%20going%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-who-will-qualify-second-attempt-biden-education-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701724597000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656e2b9c7a3c8094d5d95ae9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-who-will-qualify-second-attempt-biden-education-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Education%20Department%20released%20updated%20details%20on%20the%20student-loan%20borrowers%20who%20could%20qualify%20for%20Biden's%20second%20attempt%20at%20debt%20relief.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey