n%20locating%20the%20vika.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLocal%20knowledge%20was%20essential%20because%20this%20is%20a%20rare%20species%2C%20and%20it's%20also%20a%20challenging%20environment%20to%20conduct%20research%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Lavery%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20at%20Zaira%20told%20the%20researchers%20the%20rats%20sleep%20in%20a%20species%20of%20tree%20called%20a%20Dillenia%2C%20which%20often%20have%20hollows%20in%20their%20branches.%20In%20addition%20to%20coconuts%2C%20the%20vika%20also%20eat%20the%20local%20ngali%20nut%20(Canarium%20indicium).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Vangunu%20giant%20rat%2C%20Uromys%20vika%2C%20crawls%20on%20a%20tree%20in%20the%20Solomon%20Islands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656e26330ec98e92f74bd12c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Vangunu%20giant%20rat%20is%20critically%20endangered%2C%20and%20logging%20has%20destroyed%20its%20habitat.%3Cp%3ETyrone%20Lavery%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20placed%20their%20cameras%20accordingly%2C%20with%20most%20of%20them%20located%20high%20in%20the%20trees.%20Using%20a%20lamp%20stocked%20with%20sesame%20oil%20helped%20lure%20out%20the%20rats%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recognition%20of%20the%20local%20knowledge%20that%20assisted%20them%2C%20the%20scientists%20named%20the%20species%20Uromys%20vika.%20Vika%20is%20the%20existing%20Indigenous%20epithet%20for%20the%20giant%20rats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERats%20that%20live%20like%20monkeys%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaribbean-island-redonda-rats-restoration-wildlife-endangered-species-antigua-barbuda-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvasive%20rats%20that%20destroy%20island%20ecosystems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Vangunu%20giant%20rat%20has%20lived%20in%20the%20region%20for%20millions%20of%20years%20and%20is%20part%20of%20the%20food%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20DNA%20testing%2C%20researchers%20believe%20the%20vika%20arrived%20in%20the%20Solomon%20Island%20region%20around%203%20million%20years%20ago.%20%26quot%3BUromys%20vika%20has%20been%20isolated%20on%20Vangunu%20for%20around%201%20million%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Lavery%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20ancestors%20likely%20hitched%20a%20ride%20on%20a%20floating%20raft%20of%20vegetation%2C%20traveling%20from%20New%20Guinea%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20environment%20that%20was%20mostly%20forest%2C%20it%20made%20sense%20for%20the%20rats%20to%20live%20in%20the%20trees.%20The%20only%20other%20mammals%20in%20the%20Solomon%20Islands%20were%20bats%2C%20Lavery%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20rats%20evolved%20to%20carry%20out%20similar%20roles%20that%20belong%20to%20possums%20or%20monkeys%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20also%20likely%20solitary%20animals%2C%20Lavery%20said%2C%20because%20they%20were%20photographed%20separately%20rather%20than%20in%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvangunu-giant-rat-first-photographs-vika-endangered-species-solomon-islands-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701724127000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656e345b7a3c8094d5d96392%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvangunu-giant-rat-first-photographs-vika-endangered-species-solomon-islands-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20years%20of%20attempts%2C%20researchers%20photographed%20the%20Vangunu%20giant%20rat%2C%20which%20has%20had%20its%20habitat%20destroyed%20by%20logging%20on%20the%20Solomon%20Islands.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A41%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3