sion%20to%20sponsor%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20It%20is%20estimated%20this%20change%20with%20reduce%20arrivals%20on%20this%20route%20by%20more%20than%2020%20per%20cent%20by%202024-25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Increasing%20the%20earnings%20threshold%20by%20a%20third%20to%2038%2C700%20pounds%20from%20next%20Spring%20for%20those%20using%20the%20skilled%20worker%20route%2C%20in%20line%20with%20the%20median%20full-time%20wage%20for%20these%20kinds%20of%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Scrapping%20cut-price%20shortage%20labour%20from%20overseas%2C%20by%20ending%20the%2020%20per%20cent%20going%20rate%20salary%20discount%20for%20shortage%20occupations%20and%20reforming%20the%20Shortage%20Occupation%20List.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20We%20will%20more%20than%20double%20the%20minimum%20income%20for%20family%20visas%20to%2038%2C700%20pounds%20-%20the%20same%20threshold%20as%20the%20minimum%20salary%20threshold%20for%20skilled%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20Tightening%20the%20rules%20on%20students%20bringing%20family%20members%20to%20the%20UK.%20The%20Migration%20Advisory%20Committee%20will%20also%20review%20the%20graduate%20route.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sunak%20has%20long%20described%20regular%20immigration%20levels%20as%20%26quot%3Btoo%20high%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmigration%20-%20long%20a%20vexed%20political%20issue%20in%20Britain%20-%20is%20set%20to%20be%20a%20key%20issue%20in%20a%20general%20election%20expected%20next%20year%2C%20which%20the%20main%20opposition%20Labour%20Party%20is%20currently%20a%20favourite%20to%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20migration%20has%20soared%20since%20Britain%20formally%20left%20the%20European%20Union%20in%20January%202020.%20In%202021%2C%20net%20migration%20was%20488%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20the%20record%20number%20of%20legal%20migrants%2C%20Mr%20Sunak%20is%20struggling%20to%20cut%20the%20number%20of%20irregular%20arrivals%20crossing%20the%20Channel%20from%20northern%20France%20on%20small%20boats.%3C%2F