t%20action%20ever.%20Instead%2C%20such%20murders%20are%20based%20on%20guilt%20by%20association%2C%20and%20because%20they%20are%20attacks%20on%20homes%2C%20also%20on%20the%20families%20of%20these%20people%20as%20well%20as%20anybody%20living%20in%20the%20same%20building.%20Worse%2C%20of%20course%2C%20are%20the%20attacks%20on%20what%20the%20Israeli%20military%20classifies%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpower%20targets%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20are%20mainly%20civilian%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%93%20high-rise%20buildings%2C%20banks%2C%20even%20post%20offices%20%E2%80%93%20so%20civilians%20put%20pressure%20on%20Hamas.%20In%20legal%20terms%2C%20this%20is%20what%20is%20known%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasebook.icrc.org%2Fa_to_z%2Fglossary%2Fcollective-punishments%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecollective%20punishment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhy-all-civilian-lives-matter-equally-according-to-a-military-ethicist-218686%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeliberate%20targeting%20of%20non-combatants%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20war%20crimes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20will%20not%20be%20difficult%20for%20pro-Palestinian%20groups%20to%20draw%20a%20straight%20line%20with%20the%20helicarriers%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Winter%20Soldier%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20governing%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20as%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2022%2F06%2F14%2Fgaza-israels-open-air-prison-15%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98open-air%20prison%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20And%20it%20will%20be%20even%20easier%20to%20compare%20the%20Hydra%20algorithm%20and%20Habsora%2C%20with%20the%20added%20horror%20of%20the%20many%2C%20many%20civilian%20casualties%20of%20the%20attacks%20on%20%E2%80%9Cpower%20targets%E2%80%9D.%20But%20where%20is%20Captain%20America%20in%20all%20of%20this%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20certainly%20isn%E2%80%99t%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%20With%20his%20age%20and%20insistence%20on%20backing%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20solution%2C%20he%20would%2C%20instead%2C%20look%20very%20much%20like%20the%20character%20played%20by%20Robert%20Redford%2C%20the%20key%20villain%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Winter%20Soldier%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20who%20thinks%20diplomacy%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cband-aid%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20associations%20are%20important%20primarily%20because%20of%20how%20large%20a%20role%20comic%20book%20characters%20have%20in%20shaping%20American%20public%20opinion.%20With%20its%20multiple%20immigrant%20communities%20and%20hugely%20diminished%20native%20population%2C%20the%20US%20has%20few%20connecting%20mythologies%20on%20which%20to%20draw%20moral%20lessons.%20Comic%20book%20characters%20have%20filled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgwhatchet.com%2F2005%2F04%2F18%2Fcomic-books-the-american-mythology%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20gap%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%E2%80%98Captain%20America%E2%80%99%20created%20by%20Joe%20Simon%20and%20Jack%20Kirby%20%E2%80%93%20both%20immigrants%20of%20Jewish%20descent%20%E2%80%93%20stands%20out%20as%20one%20of%20the%20few%20explicitly%20political%20characters%2C%20and%20he%20was%20created%20not%20just%20to%20oppose%20Hitler%2C%20but%20also%20to%20advocate%20against%20the%20then%20policy%20of%20the%20United%20States%20which%20was%20to%20not%20get%20involved%20in%20World%20War%20II.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Funited-states-israel-palestine%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20Is%20Part%20of%20the%20Problem%20in%20Israel-Palestine%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20literally%20being%20dressed%20in%20the%20American%20flag%2C%20and%20a%20staple%20for%20WWII%20propaganda%2C%20Captain%20America%20has%20often%20been%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20US%20establishment.%20Nowhere%20was%20this%20made%20clearer%20than%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.polygon.com%2Fcomics%2F2017%2F5%2F11%2F15615614%2Fmarvel-secret-empire-watergate-steve-englehart%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E1974%20series%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20where%20the%20villain%20is%20strongly%20implied%20to%20be%20US%20President%20Richard%20Nixon.%20In%20a%20recent%20run%2C%20Captain%20America%20fights%20off%20White%20racists%20on%20the%20US-Mexico%20border%20to%20help%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.polygon.com%2Fcomics%2F2019%2F9%2F3%2F20847404%2Fcaptain-america-marvel-comics-illegal-migrants-black-panther-doctor-strange%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eundocumented%20migrants%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20And%20the%20best%20parts%20of%20the%202021%20TV%20series%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Falcon%20and%20the%20Winter%20Soldier%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20in%20which%20a%20Black%20man%20picks%20up%20Captain%20America%E2%80%99s%20mantle%20(and%20shield)%2C%20looked%20at%20America%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2021%2F04%2F29%2Fopinions%2Ffalcon-and-the-winter-soldier-black-captain-america-joseph%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elong%20history%20of%20racism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20leaders%20of%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20protests%20have%20explicitly%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fhow-black-lives-matter-is-changing-the-conversation-on-palestine-161429%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ealigned%20with%20Palestinians%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECaptain%20America%2C%20as%20a%20character%2C%20has%20been%20a%20way%20of%20defining%20for%20many%20young%20and%20not-so-young%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.gitnux.com%2Fcomic-book-demographic-statistics%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaverage%20age%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20comic%20book%20readers%20is%2035%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20American%20readers%20what%20America%20should%20be%2C%20not%20what%20it%20is.%20The%20scenes%20being%20broadcast%20from%20the%20war%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20will%20be%20interpreted%20through%20such%20lenses.%20While%20the%20evidence%20of%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20brutality%20against%20civilians%20during%20October%207%20will%20resonate%2C%20so%20too%20will%20the%20images%20of%20Palestinian%20civilians%20digging%20out%20the%20body%20parts%20of%20their%20loved%20ones%20from%20the%20ruins%20of%20their%20homes.%20It%20is%20thus%20understandable%20that%2C%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2F16%2Fisrael-palestine-quinnipiac-poll-00127726%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20recent%20US%20poll%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Crespondents%20under%2035%20years%20old%E2%80%A6%20overwhelmingly%20said%20they%20disapprove%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20Oct.%207%20Hamas%20attack%20(66%25)%2C%20have%20greater%20sympathy%20for%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20conflict%20than%20Israelis%20(52%25)%20and%20believe%20the%20US%20is%20too%20supportive%20of%20Israel%20(50%25).%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20the%20Israeli%20prime%20minister%2C%20has%20long%20prided%20himself%20on%20being%20able%20to%20manage%20the%20US%20establishment.%20In%202021%20he%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jta.org%2F2021%2F06%2F02%2Fisrael%2Fnetanyahu-changed-the-way-americans-view-israel-but-not-always-in-the-way-he-wanted%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eeven%20boasted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20know%20what%20America%20is.%20America%20is%20a%20thing%20you%20can%20move%20very%20easily%2C%20move%20it%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%E2%80%9D%20He%20may%20be%20correct%20insofar%20as%20the%20political%20establishment%20in%20the%20US%20is%20concerned%2C%20but%20does%20he%20know%20Captain%20America%3F%20That%20might%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20be%20far%20more%20important.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EP.S.%20The%20upcoming%20Captain%20America%20film%20is%20supposed%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2022%2F09%2F14%2Fmiddleeast%2Fmarvel-israeli-superhero-mime-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edepict%20the%20first%20Israeli%20superhero%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20Marvel%20Cinematic%20Universe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fomair-ahmad%5C%22%3EOmair%20Ahmad%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701690319000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19101948%2FF8uduyaWoAAr3mW.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-palestine-war-benjamin-netanyahu-captain-america-problem%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pop%20culture%20references%20of%20right%20and%20wrong%2C%20particularly%20through%20comic%20book%20characters%20like%20Captain%20America%2C%20will%20profoundly%20shape%20the%20feelings%20of%20younger%20Americans%20in%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-palestine-war-benjamin-netanyahu-captain-america-problem%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Making%20Disability%20a%20Joke%20Is%20Neither%20Comedy%20Nor%20Art%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04162855%2Fcap.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sat%20through%20roughly%20two%20and%20a%20half%20hours%20of%20crisis%20while%20watching%20the%20recent%20Bollywood%20movie%20%3Cem%3EAankh%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EMicholi%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Recently%2C%20Goa%20State%20Commissioner%20for%20Persons%20with%20Disabilities%20ordered%20two%20district%20administrations%20to%20stop%20the%20movie%20from%20screening.%20The%20office%20of%20the%20Chief%20Commissioner%20of%20Persons%20with%20Disabilities%20also%20issued%20notice%20to%20the%20makers%20of%20the%20movie%20and%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Film%20Certification%20seeking%20a%20response%20from%20them%2C%20as%20the%20movie%20violated%20Sections%203%20(non-discrimination)%20and%2092%20(punishment%20for%20offences%20of%20atrocities)%20of%20the%20Rights%20of%20Person%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%2C%202016%20(RPwD%20Act).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20brief%2C%20the%20story%20is%20based%20on%20a%20family%20of%20six.%20Barring%20two%20members%2C%20all%20of%20them%20live%20with%20some%20form%20of%20disability.%20%C2%A0The%20story%20is%20premised%20on%20the%20theme%20of%20the%20marriage%20of%20the%20lead%20character%20(Mrunal%20Thakur)%2C%20who%20is%20living%20with%20a%20visual%20disability%2C%20rendering%20her%20unable%20to%20see%20at%20night.%20The%20underlying%20premise%20is%20that%20the%20disability%20is%20a%20disease%20that%20has%20to%20be%20hidden%20from%20outsiders%20(including%20the%20one%20you%20will%20be%20marrying).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUndoing%20the%20understanding%20of%20disability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disability%20movement%20across%20generations%20has%20struggled%20to%20eradicate%20the%20engrained%20idea%20of%20the%20medical%20model%20of%20disability%2C%20wherein%20your%20disability%20is%20identified%20in%20the%20medical%20condition.%20The%20American%20civil%20rights%20movement%20percolated%20into%20the%20disability%20rights%20movement.%20Thus%2C%20the%20social%20model%20of%20disability%20was%20followed%2C%20wherein%20societal%20barriers%20are%20identified%20as%20the%20source%20of%20disability%20and%20not%20the%20individual.%20This%20understanding%20was%20implemented%20through%20legislative%20mandate%20under%20the%20Rights%20of%20Persons%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%2C%202016%2C%20which%20used%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Cperson%20with%20disability%E2%80%9D%20rather%20than%20a%20disabled%20person%20%E2%80%93%20placing%20individuals%20at%20the%20forefront.%20It%20also%20defines%20a%20person%20with%20disability%20in%20a%20more%20social%20sense%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ea%20person%20with%20long-term%20physical%2C%20mental%2C%20intellectual%20or%20sensory%20impairment%20which%2C%20in%20%3Cstrong%3Einteraction%20with%20barriers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20hinders%20his%20full%20and%20effective%20participation%20in%20society%20equally%20with%20others%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20makers%20of%20this%20movie%20and%20others%20in%20the%20Indian%20cinema%20world%20have%20systematically%20misconstrued%20this%20fundamental%20differentiation.%20In%20the%20movie%2C%20characters%20often%20view%20the%20inherent%20disability%20as%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20characteristic%20and%20a%20painful%20extra.%20Disability%20is%20termed%20a%20%3Cem%3Ebeemari%3C%2Fem%3E%20(disease).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20legal%20excuse%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apparent%20argument%20from%20the%20makers%20of%20the%20movie%20is%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20creative%20liberty.%20This%20overarching%20freedom%20is%20also%20limited%20by%20reasonable%20limitation%20under%20Article%2019(2)%2C%20specifically%20decency%20and%20morality.%20The%20makers%20have%20rendered%20the%20creation%20an%20ideal%20piece%20of%20ableism%20devoid%20of%20decency.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20proactively%20decided%20not%20to%20confine%20the%20contours%20of%20decency%20to%20just%20acts%20of%20a%20sexual%20nature%20but%20has%20widened%20the%20horizons%20to%20include%20acts%20that%20would%20invite%20a%20collective%20shock%2C%20disgust%20or%20revolt.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F925631%2F%5C%22%3EDr.%20Ramesh%20Yeshwant%20Prabhoo%20vs%20Shri%20Prabhakar%20Kashinath%20Kunte%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20while%20explaining%20indecency%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%3Cem%3EIndecency%20is%20not%20confined%20to%20sexual%20indecency%3B%20indeed%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20find%20any%20limit%20short%20of%20saying%20that%20it%20includes%20anything%20which%20an%20ordinary%20decent%20man%20or%20woman%20would%20find%20to%20be%20shocking%2C%20disgusting%20and%20revolting%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20makers%20in%20the%20work%20employ%20the%20ableist%20framework%20in%20every%20corner%20of%20the%20screenplay%2C%20garbed%20as%20humour.%20This%20fundamentally%20invites%20disgust%20from%20a%20large%20sect%20of%20society%20whose%20lives%20are%20depicted%20as%20devoid%20of%20any%20dignity.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fjournal%2Fsco-explains-vikash-kumar-v-upsc%2F%5C%22%3EVikash%20Kumar%20vs%20UPSC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20while%20explaining%20the%20dignity%20of%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20said%20that%20it%20is%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Cintrinsic%20to%20individual%20dignity.%20is%20recognising%20the%20worth%20of%20every%20person%20as%20an%20equal%20member%20of%20the%20society%2C%20respect%20for%20the%20dignity%20of%20others%20and%20fostering%20conditions%20in%20which%20every%20individual%20can%20evolve%20according%20to%20his%20capabilities%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%80%98Sam%20Bahadur%E2%80%99%3A%20Yet%20Another%20Biopic%20That%20Is%20in%20Awe%20of%20Its%20Protagonist%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fsam-bahadur-biopic-review-meghan-gulzar-vicky-kaushal%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Sam%20Bahadur%E2%80%99%3A%20Yet%20Another%20Biopic%20That%20Is%20in%20Awe%20of%20Its%20Protagonist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%205B%20of%20the%20Cinematograph%20Act%2C%201952%20deals%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98Principles%20of%20guidance%20in%20certifying%20films%E2%80%99.%20Subsection%20(1)%20of%20section%205B%20allows%20the%20film%20certification%20authorities%20to%20not%20certify%20a%20film%20for%20public%20exhibition%20if%20it%20is%20against%20%E2%80%9Cdecency%20and%20morality%E2%80%9D.%20This%20can%20serve%20as%20an%20instrument%20to%20direct%20makers%20to%20comply%20with%20basic%20tenets%20of%20dignity%20wherein%20creativity%20subordinates%20every%20other%20aspect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RPwD%20Act%20was%20implemented%20to%20ensure%20equality%20and%20dignity%20for%20persons%20with%20disabilities.%20Resultantly%2C%20section%203%20of%20the%20RPwD%20Act%20talks%20about%20equality%20and%20non-discrimination.%20It%20is%20operationalised%20in%20different%20sectors%20through%20various%20sections%20of%20the%20RPwD%20Act%2C%20wherein%20government%20and%20private%20bodies%20are%20obligated%20to%20ensure%20this%20mandate.%20%C2%A0Thus%2C%20the%20Cinematograph%20Act%20must%20be%20aligned%20with%20these%20principles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreating%20stereotype%20through%20cinema%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20phenomenon%20is%20not%20new%20and%20is%20documented%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstanford.edu%2F~kartiks2%2FdisabilityInBollywood.pdf%5C%22%3Eseminal%20piece%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Joyojeet%20Pal.%20He%20underlines%20four%20trends%20in%20Indian%20films%3A%20first%2C%20disability%20as%20punitive%3B%20second%2C%20disability%20as%20dependence%3B%20third%2C%20disability%20as%20disequilibrium%20and%20fourth%2C%20disability%20as%20maladjustment.%20For%20the%20first%20trend%2C%20an%20all-time%20classic%20%3Cem%3ESholay%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1975)%20fits%20the%20mould%3B%20the%20antagonist%20thinks%20chopping%20off%20a%20character%E2%80%99s%20arms%20is%20worse%20than%20death.%20Disability%20as%20a%20divine%20punishment%20has%20also%20been%20a%20central%20theme%20for%20makers%2C%20which%20is%20visible%20in%20movies%20like%20%3Cem%3EDhanwaan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1981).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20aspect%2C%20and%20probably%20the%20most%20prominent%20one%2C%20is%20of%20disability%20as%20dependence.%20The%20sympathetic%20attitude%20towards%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20is%20often%20transformed%20into%20the%20object%20of%20pity%20and%20a%20metaphor%20depicting%20helplessness.%20This%20is%20catalysed%20by%20cinematic%20depiction.%20Pal%2C%20in%20his%20paper%2C%20underscores%20a%20series%20of%20films%20that%20have%20regularly%20employed%20this%20trend%2C%20mainly%20as%20a%20subject%20of%20violence%20because%20of%20this%20dependence%2C%20like%20in%20%3Cem%3EHum%20Aapko%20Aapse%20Pyaar%20Hai%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2006)%20or%20an%20all-time%20classic%20like%20%3Cem%3EMother%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1957)%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20wherein%20the%20disability%20is%20looked%20at%20with%20ridicule%20as%20it%20is%20presumed%20to%20default%20dependence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20and%20fourth%20aspects%20are%20closely%20related%20to%20finding%20disability%20as%20something%20extra%20that%20burdens%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20live%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnormal%E2%80%9D%20life%20in%20a%20society.%20This%20is%20evidenced%20in%20the%20screenplays%20where%20the%20protagonist%E2%80%99s%20sole%20objective%20is%20to%20either%20correct%20her%2Fhis%20disability%20or%20that%20of%20someone%20else.%20This%20is%20vividly%20visible%20in%20Shatrughan%20Sinha%E2%80%99s%20movie%20%3Cem%3EAa%20Gale%20Lag%20Jaa%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1974)%2C%20where%20he%20endeavours%20to%20cure%20a%20polio-struck%20boy%20by%20employing%20the%20most%20extreme%20form%20of%20mental%20violence.%20Thus%2C%20as%20Pal%20mentions%20in%20his%20paper%2C%20there%20is%20a%20dearth%20of%20cinema%20wherein%20the%20protagonist%20stays%20disabled%20throughout%20the%20film.%20Recent%20creations%20like%20%3Cem%3EMargarita%20with%20a%20Straw%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2014)%20or%20%3Cem%3EGuzaarish%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2010)%20serve%20as%20an%20exception%20on%20this%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Animal%3A%20Sandeep%20Reddy%20Vanga%E2%80%99s%20Crude%20and%20Beastly%20Assault%20on%20Sense%20and%20Sensibility%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fanimal-sandeep-reddy-vangas-crude-and-beastly-assault-on-sense-and-sensibility%5C%22%3EAnimal%3A%20Sandeep%20Reddy%20Vanga%E2%80%99s%20Crude%20and%20Beastly%20Assault%20on%20Sense%20and%20Sensibility%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20social%20maladjustment%20aspect%20of%20disability%20further%20attributes%20the%20trait%20of%20evilness.%20This%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Freel%2F1007109%2Fwhy-a-disfigured-or-disabled-screen-villain-is-an-idea-that-needs-to-die%5C%22%3Enot%20unique%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Indian%20films%2C%20as%20the%20recent%20addition%20to%20James%20Bond%E2%80%99s%20franchise%20showed%20Rame%20Malek%20as%20having%20a%20disability%20to%20underline%20his%20evil%20characters%20further.%20However%2C%20the%20most%20common%20usage%C2%A0%20of%20this%20aspect%20in%20in%20comedy%2C%20which%20is%20exactly%20what%20makers%20of%3Cem%3E%20Aankh%20Micholi%3C%2Fem%3E%20intended%20to%20do.%20A%20few%20examples%20include%20%3Cem%3EHum%20Hai%20Kamaal%20ke%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1993)%20or%20%3Cem%3ETom%20Dick%20and%20Harry%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2006)%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20makers%20of%20%3Cem%3EAankh%20Micholi%3C%2Fem%3E%20indulge%20in%20establishing%20the%20undertone%20that%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20are%20not%20necessarily%20equal%2C%20especially%20when%20they%20have%20to%20fit%20into%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage.%20The%20underlying%20messaging%20%C2%A0of%20the%20film%20%E2%80%93%20that%20to%20fit%20in%20the%20most%20fundamental%20unit%20of%20our%20society%2C%20people%20with%20disabilities%20must%20hide%20their%20disability%20%E2%80%93%20cannot%20be%20overlooked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERespect%20the%20new%20reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHindi%20cinema%20has%20seen%20a%20transition%20to%20accommodate%20disability%20more%20meaningfully%20and%20is%20sticking%20to%20a%20new%20understanding%20of%20the%20concept.%20This%20understanding%20is%20depicted%20in%20films%20like%20%3Cem%3EBlack%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2005)%20and%20%3Cem%3EMy%20Name%20is%20Khan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2010).%20The%20makers%20don%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20have%20to%20overwrite%20disability%20in%20their%20screenplay%20for%20any%20of%20the%20four%20trends%20mentioned%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Bollywood%20wants%20to%20make%20a%20comedy%20using%20disability%20as%20the%20central%20theme%2C%20they%20might%20wish%20to%20experiment%20with%20an%20extreme%20option%3A%20casting%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%20In%20the%20movies%20%3Cem%3EPeanut%20Butter%20Falcon%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2019)%20or%20%3Cem%3EGive%20me%20Liberty%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2019)%2C%20an%20actor%20with%20Down%20Syndrome%20and%20locomotor%20disability%20shows%20that%20comedic%20timing%20is%20not%20the%20exclusive%20domain%20of%20able-bodied%20individuals%20but%20rather%20a%20skill%20to%20be%20acquired%20with%20effort.%20It%20might%20not%20have%20to%20look%20far%20for%20inspiration%20either.%20Gulzar%E2%80%99s%201972%20classic%20%3Cem%3EKoshish%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20its%20poster%20and%20introduction%20credits%20in%20sign%20language%2C%20as%20the%20lead%20actors%20were%20living%20with%20some%20form%20of%20disability.%20The%20character%20depicted%20that%20they%20can%20live%20independently%20if%20society%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20interfere.%20This%20conceptual%20understanding%20was%20far%20ahead%20in%20both%20cinematic%20and%20political%20discourse.%20The%20decline%20of%20Indian%20cinema%20from%20%3Cem%3EKoshish%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20%3Cem%3EAankh%20Micholi%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20disability%20depiction%20shows%20the%20intellectual%20bankruptcy%20of%20today%E2%80%99s%20makers.%20Making%20disability%20a%20joke%20is%20neither%20comedy%20nor%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShashank%20Pandey%20is%20a%20lawyer%20and%20policy%20researcher%20working%20on%20the%20cases%20of%20disability%20issues.%20He%20is%20also%20a%20person%20with%20Low%20Vision%20disability.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701689403000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04162855%2Fcap.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fmaking-disability-a-joke-is-neither-comedy-nor-art%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20film%20'Aankh%20Micholi'%20portrays%20characters%20with%20disabilities%20as%20having%20a%20problem%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20hidden.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fmaking-disability-a-joke-is-neither-comedy-nor-art%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World%20War%20Two%20bomb%20detonated%20off%20coast%20of%20Denmark%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701689281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F15CB7%2Fproduction%2F_131917298_p0gxhjjk.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67613803%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20130kg%20bomb%20got%20caught%20in%20a%20fisherman's%20net%20and%20had%20to%20be%20detonated%20by%20the%20Danish%20Navy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A612%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fworld-europe-67613803%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20to%20become%20%245%20trillion%20economy%20early%20in%20Amrit%20Kaal%3A%20MoS%20Finance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701688855000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F02%2Ffull%2F1690991579-8169.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Findia-to-become-5-trillon-economy-early-in-amrit-kaal-mos-finance-123120400543_1.htm