ter%20being%20destabilised%20by%20a%20storm%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20floor%20is%20wet%20with%20the%20sea%E2%80%99s%20retreat%3Cbr%3E%5CnA%20draggled%20wing%3Cbr%3E%5Cndrapes%20its%20shadow%20on%20the%20bell%20tower%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%20Admiral%2C%20your%20telescope!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20however%2C%20you%20realise%20that%20the%20images%20and%20voices%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20surreal.%20In%20a%20remarkable%20metaphor%2C%20Hoskote%20describes%20sleep%2C%20dreaming%2C%20but%20also%20time%3A%20%E2%80%9CHe%20scoops%20darkness%20%2F%20from%20darkness%E2%80%9D.%20If%20sleep%20and%20the%20subconscious%20are%20a%20vast%2C%20black%2C%20night-time%20sea%2C%20the%20sailor%20can%20be%20imagined%20to%20be%20rowing%20through%20it%20with%20his%20paddle%2C%20scooping%20up%20the%20dark%20waters%2C%20keeping%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENautical%20images%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20not%20uncommon%20in%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20poetry.%20In%20his%20earlier%20collection%20of%20poetry%2C%20%3Cem%3EJohanwhale%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2018)%2C%20he%20had%20drawn%20upon%20the%20Biblical%20Book%20of%20Jonah%2C%20Herman%20Melville%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMoby%20Dick%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1851)%2C%20and%20nautical%20histories%20to%20create%20elegies.%20His%20previous%20book%20of%20poetry%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHunchprose%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2021)%2C%20which%20I%20had%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fbeyond-business%2Fhunchprose-hoskote-s-poems-offer-a-bastion-of-truth-in-a-post-truth-world-121040901569_1.html%5C%22%3Ereviewed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20drew%20upon%20images%20of%20oceans%20and%20voyages%20as%20metaphors%20for%20narratives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%E2%80%9CRetreat%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20image%20of%20the%20sea%20is%20not%20only%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20subconscious%20but%20also%20a%20vessel%20that%20allows%20Hoskote%20to%20travel%20between%20genres%20of%20surreal%20and%20futuristic%20poetry.%20In%20the%20last%20two%20stanzas%20of%20the%20poem%2C%20it%20is%20revealed%20that%20the%20admiral%20of%20the%20ship%20is%20not%20travelling%20between%20two%20ports%20but%20between%20two%20worlds%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20surveyor%20continues%20to%20look%3Cbr%3E%5Cnfor%20a%20world%20at%20the%20other%20end%3Cbr%3E%5Cnof%20his%20spyglass%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eknowing%20it%E2%80%99s%20out%20there%3Cbr%3E%5Cna%20distant%20cousin%20to%20the%20one%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthat%E2%80%99s%20blowing%20up%20around%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20it%20is%20not%20too%20far-fetched%20to%20imagine%20that%20the%20vessel%20is%20an%20intergalactic%20spaceship%20with%20voyagers%20escaping%20from%20Earth%20torn%20apart%20by%20conflict%20and%20the%20disastrous%20effects%20of%20climate%20change.%20There%20is%20an%20element%20of%20hope%2C%20of%20finding%20another%20planet%20that%20might%20accommodate%20humans%20when%20the%20third%20rock%20from%20the%20sun%20implodes%20because%20of%20our%20relentless%20activities.%20But%20it%20is%20also%20a%20grim%20image%2C%20of%20a%20world%20blowing%20up%20all%20around%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20months%2C%20as%20governments%20around%20the%20world%20have%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2023%2F11%2F1144127%5C%22%3Efailed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20act%20decisively%20to%20prevent%20climate%20change%20or%20stop%20conflict%20like%20the%20one%20roiling%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-israel-palestine-war-is-a-stain-on-every-one-of-us%5C%22%3EIsrael-Palestine%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20October%207%2C%20annihilation%20anxiety%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F00030651030510020801%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20psychoanalysts%20as%20%E2%80%9C(f)ears%20of%20being%20overwhelmed%2C%20merged%2C%20penetrated%2C%20fragmented%2C%20and%20destroyed%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20has%20spiked.%20Polarisation%20around%20tentpole%20events%2C%20often%20acerbated%20by%20vicious%20online%20campaigns%2C%20only%20aggravates%20such%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHoskote%20has%20experienced%20the%20effects%20of%20such%20polarising%20himself%20following%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fcurator-ranjit-hoskote-resigns-from-documentas-finding-committee-over-anti-semitism-allegations%5C%22%3Eaccusations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20antisemitism%20in%20early%20November%20this%20year%20by%20the%20German%20daily%C2%A0%3Cem%3ES%C3%BCddeutsche%20Zeitung%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20signing%20a%202019%20BDS%20(Boycott%2C%20Disinvestment%20and%20Sanctions%20against%20Israel)%20petition%20against%20an%20event%20on%20%E2%80%9CZionism%20and%20Hindutva%E2%80%9D%20organised%20by%20the%20Consulate%20General%20of%20Israel%20in%20Mumbai.%20With%20the%20German%20government%20threatening%20to%20withdraw%20funding%20for%20Documenta%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20prestigious%20art%20exhibitions%20held%20every%20five%20years%20in%20Kassel%2C%20Germany%2C%20Hoskote%20resigned%20from%20the%20Finding%20Committee%20of%20its%20upcoming%2016th%20edition.%20In%20his%20resignation%20letter%2C%20he%20clarified%20his%20position%20that%20while%20he%20did%20not%20support%20the%20intellectual%20and%20cultural%20boycott%20of%20Israel%2C%20he%20was%20also%20opposed%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20any%20criticism%20of%20the%20country%20should%20be%20painted%20as%20%E2%80%9Cantisemitism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20dedicated%20my%20life%20to%20opposing%20authoritarian%20forces%20and%20discriminatory%20ideologies%2C%20and%20my%20signature%20carried%20with%20it%20the%20weight%20of%20my%20commitment%20to%20dialogue%2C%20inclusiveness%2C%20mutuality%2C%20and%20the%20ceaseless%20quest%20for%20common%20ground%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20letter.%20But%2C%20in%20this%20age%20of%20polarising%20debates%20augmented%20by%20social%20media%20algorithms%20and%20trigger-happy%20cancel%20culture%2C%20such%20nuance%20is%20easily%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHunchprose%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Hoskote%20had%20set%20up%20a%20dichotomy%20between%20the%20poet%E2%80%99s%20nuanced%20use%20of%20language%20and%20the%20shiny%20wordplay%20of%20a%20rhetorician.%20Anxiety%20about%20the%20utility%20of%20poetry%20in%20our%20world%20%E2%80%94%20even%20the%20ability%20to%20write%20it%20%E2%80%94%20informs%20some%20of%20the%20poems%20in%20his%20book%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRedacted%E2%80%9D%20is%20haunted%20by%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20lost%20poem.%20It%20begins%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20poem%20was%20not%20found%20in%20his%20manuscripts%E2%80%9D.%20Then%2C%20a%20litany%20is%20provided%20of%20all%20the%20places%20where%20this%20poem%20is%20not%20found%3A%20%E2%80%9Cmanuscripts%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cconversations%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cinterviews%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Clectures%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Carchive%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Chard%20drives%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cxeroxes%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cindex%20cards%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20somewhat%20reminiscent%20of%20litanies%20and%20lists%20provided%20by%20the%20Chilean%20novelist%20Roberto%20Bola%C3%B1o%20in%20his%20byzantine%20novels%20about%20missing%20writers.%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20poem%20ends%20with%20the%20lines%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChased%20by%20prosecutors%20fanning%20their%20collars%3Cbr%3E%5Cnflashing%20across%20banners%20wayward%20as%20the%20wind%3Cbr%3E%5Cnnothing%20conclusive%20you%20understand%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthis%20poem%20may%20never%20be%20found%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20almost%20a%20nightmarish%20conclusion%20of%20silencing%2C%20of%20censorship%2C%20that%20might%20give%20sleepless%20nights%20to%20editors%2C%20literary%20scholars%2C%20and%20textual%20historians.%20How%20do%20you%20respond%20to%20a%20poem%20that%20is%20never%20found%3F%20What%20is%20the%20value%20of%20a%20lost%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20theme%20Hoskote%20returns%20to%20a%20little%20later%20in%20the%20book%2C%20in%20the%20poem%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Harappan%20Merchant%E2%80%99s%20Complaint%E2%80%9D.%20The%20titular%20merchant%20begins%20by%20demanding%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20do%20I%20care%20how%20these%20words%20sound%3Cbr%3E%5Cnin%20translation%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EJoppo%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekshumpa%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eplaksha%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20detailed%20endnotes%20on%20this%20poem%2C%20Hoskote%20explains%20that%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ejoppo%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0means%20water%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekshumpa%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20mushroom%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eplaksha%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20the%20fig%20tree.%20While%20the%20first%20one%20appears%20in%20Nihali%2C%20%E2%80%9Can%20endangered%20Central%20Indian%20language%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20others%20are%20found%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3ERig%20Veda%3C%2Fem%3E.%20All%20three%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20the%20language%20of%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20Civilisation%20that%20has%20eluded%20decipherment%20over%20the%20century%20since%20its%20discovery.%20Naturally%2C%20the%20Harappan%20merchant%20throws%20the%20gauntlet%20to%20the%20reader%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20decipher%20if%20you%20dare%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthese%20words%20sealed%20in%20images%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthe%20squat%20bull%20the%20sage%20lost%20in%20a%20trance%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ethe%20horned%20man%20fighting%20a%20tiger%3Cbr%3E%5CnAre%20these%20chants%20to%20cure%20the%20seasick%3Cbr%3E%5Cnor%20curses%20aimed%20at%20fleeing%20debtors%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20Harappan%20language%20is%20now%20lost%20to%20us%2C%20will%20our%20language%20also%20be%20lost%20to%20future%20generations%3F%20This%20anxiety%20is%20particularly%20poignant%20for%20someone%20like%20Hoskote%2C%20who%20is%20not%20only%20a%20poet%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIcelight%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20his%20eighth%20collection%20of%20poetry%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20an%20accomplished%20translator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20poem%2C%20%E2%80%9CPaishachi%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20ghazal%20of%20sorts%2C%20refers%20to%20the%20legendary%20language%20of%20ghosts%20from%20which%20Kashmiri%20is%20said%20to%20have%20descended.%20All%20the%20couplets%20in%20this%20poem%20end%20with%20the%20refrain%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20language%20of%20ghosts%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20words%20sound%20like%20nothing%20that%20guests%20have%20ever%20spoken%20to%20hosts.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThis%20is%20the%20language%20of%20my%20people%2C%20the%20language%20of%20living%20ghosts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20violence%20is%20not%20only%20epistemically%20experienced%3B%20it%20is%20also%20corporeal.%20The%20poem%20%E2%80%9CLesson%E2%80%9D%2C%20dedicated%20to%20Kashmiri%20poet%20and%20filmmaker%20Asiya%20Zahoor%2C%20also%20refers%20to%20the%20troubled%20region%20of%20Kashmir%20and%20the%20suppression%20of%20free%20speech.%20In%20the%20poem%2C%20a%20professor%20admonishes%20his%20class%2C%20asking%20them%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20to%20say%20a%20word%E2%80%9D.%20His%20chalk%20bifurcates%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20a%20metaphoric%20reference%20to%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2019%2F9%2F4%2Findia-revokes-kashmirs-special-status%5C%22%3Eunilateral%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202019%20to%20revoke%20Article%20370%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20that%20gave%20the%20region%20some%20degree%20of%20autonomy%20and%20the%20bifurcation%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20This%20decision%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20brutal%2C%20months-long%20communications%20lockdown%20in%20the%20region%20that%20Hoskote%20reimagines%20poetically%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20clapped%20his%20hands%20and%20blew%20on%20them%3Cbr%3E%5Cncould%20of%20chalk%20dust%20settled%20on%20our%20desks%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eburying%20them%20for%20years%20in%20snow%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20the%20image%20he%20chooses%20to%20express%20the%20aesthetics%20of%20poetry%20in%20this%20book%20%E2%80%94%20which%20I%20call%20%E2%80%9Cannihilation%20aesthetics%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20is%20light%20refracted%20through%20ice.%20There%20is%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20loss%20that%20shoots%20through%20the%20poems%2C%20many%20are%20dedicated%20to%20people%20who%20have%20died%20recently.%20The%20book%20is%20dedicated%20to%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20who%20died%20in%202021.%20At%20least%20three%20poems%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%9CAubade%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CBreath%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9CBed%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20were%20earlier%20published%20in%20an%20anthology%20on%20the%20pandemic%20and%20lockdown%2C%20edited%20by%20K.%20Satchidanandan%20and%20Nishi%20Chawla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20first%20poem%20expresses%20a%20desire%20to%20disappear%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20if%20there%20was%20no%20border%3Cbr%3E%5Cnbetween%20flesh%20and%20light%3Cbr%3E%5CnWhat%20if%20I%20had%3Cbr%3E%5Cnno%20skin%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObjects%2C%20including%20human%20beings%2C%20can%20be%20seen%20because%20light%20reflects%20on%20them%3B%20turning%20transparent%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20also%20a%20process%20of%20turning%20invisible.%20This%20image%20sustains%20throughout%20the%20book%2C%20a%20light%20so%20refracted%20and%20otherworldly%20that%20it%20is%20difficult%20not%20to%20be%20blinded%20by%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20final%20poem%20of%20the%20book%2C%20%E2%80%9CReturn%E2%80%9D%2C%20Hoskote%20leaves%20us%20with%20a%20post-apocalyptic%20vision%20of%20the%20world.%20A%20ship%20abandoned%20in%20the%20clouds%2C%20without%20any%20captain%20or%20crew%20or%20compass%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eas%20you%20stumble%20towards%20the%20latched%20gate%3Cbr%3E%5Cnout-of-breath%20traveller%3Cbr%3E%5Cnstammering%20a%20word%20of%20thanks%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Elight%20returns%20to%20the%20world%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20this%20the%20light%20of%20a%20fadeout%20%E2%80%94%20a%20white%20darkness%20of%20sorts%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20film%20that%20leaves%20you%20gobsmacked%20(this%20book%20definitely%20does)%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20a%20metaphor%20for%20hope%2C%20of%20renewal%3F%20One%20must%20believe%20that%20it%20is%2C%20simply%20to%20carry%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUttaran%20Das%20Gupta%20is%20a%20New%20Delhi-based%20writer%20and%20journalist.%20He%20teaches%20journalism%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20Sonipat.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701676841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04122322%2FRH-Icelight.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fverse-affairs-annihilation-aesthetics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ranjit%20Hoskote%E2%80%99s%20latest%20collection%20of%20poetry%C2%A0'Icelight'%C2%A0explores%20pandemic%20and%20global%20warming-induced%20annihilation%20anxiety%20but%20finds%20refuge%20in%20poetry%20and%20language.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fverse-affairs-annihilation-aesthetics%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine%20war%3A%20Soldier%20tells%20BBC%20of%20front-line%20'hell'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701668737000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F17124%2Fproduction%2F_131900549_gettyimages-1677802503.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67565508%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20on%20the%20east%20side%20of%20the%20Dnipro%20river%20tells%20the%20BBC%20about%20life%20on%20the%20front%20line.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A319%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67565508%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67565508.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67565508.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi%20has%20turned%20a%20custom%20of%20Indian%20politics%20on%2